radiographic_examinations.findings: There is minimal atelectasis at the lung bases. The appendix is dilated and hyperemic measuring 12 mm with surrounding stranding and a small amount of fluid in the right lower quadrant consistent with appendicitis. There is no definite evidence of perforation. Multiple hepatic hypodensities are too small to characterize but most likely cysts. The kidneys have dilation of the right renal pelvis and minimal blunting of the calyces. No free fluid or lymphadenopathy within the abdomen and pelvis. No bony lesions concerning for malignancy.
